{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180950896,"sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","part":{"id":"prt_c9e374c560017F3LM6EGMJI29m","sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","messageID":"msg_c9e374479001J2uXjvyO7QyS10","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01CRf6RpTnm3kQhPRQ3gbZkH","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/run-state.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/run-state.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Run State\n2: \n3: > Persists per-run artifacts: timestamped run directory, live `session.json`,\n4: > JSONL event log, and per-iteration transcripts.\n5: \n6: **Source:** `src/run-state.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: The run-state module creates and maintains the file-based record of a single\n11: engine run. It is the write side of the run artifact system; `src/run-status.ts`\n12: is the corresponding read side. A `RunTracker` instance is created at the\n13: start of each engine run and holds the run directory open for the duration,\n14: flushing state after every event and appending event records to an append-only\n15: JSONL log.\n16: \n17: ## Triggers\n18: \n19: - `startRunTracker(projectDir, description, maxIterations)` â€” called by the\n20:   Engine at the beginning of every run. (`src/engine.ts`)\n21: - `RunTracker.recordEvent(event)` â€” called by the Engine each time an\n22:   `EngineEvent` is emitted.\n23: - `RunTracker.writeIterationTranscript(iteration, label, rawOutput?,\n24:   displayOutput?)` â€” called by the Engine after each iteration completes.\n25: - `RunTracker.finalize(status)` â€” called by the Engine in its `finally`\n26:   block when the run ends.\n27: \n28: ## Inputs\n29: \n30: | Name | Type | Source | Description |\n31: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n32: | `projectDir` | `string` | Engine | Absolute path to the project root |\n33: | `description` | `string` | phase `setup` return | Human-readable description of the run |\n34: | `maxIterations` | `number` | phase `setup` return | Upper bound on iterations for this run |\n35: | `event` | `EngineEvent` | Engine event emitter | Typed engine lifecycle event to record |\n36: | `iteration` | `number` | Engine | Iteration index (1-based) |\n37: | `label` | `string` | Engine | Short label identifying the iteration (e.g., bead ID or title) |\n38: | `rawOutput` | `string \\| undefined` | `src/output-parser.ts` | Raw JSON event log from the session |\n39: | `displayOutput` | `string \\| undefined` | `src/output-parser.ts` | Human-readable session transcript |\n40: | `status` | `string` | Engine | Final run status string written to `session.json` |\n41: \n42: ## Outputs\n43: \n44: | Name | Type | Destination | Description |\n45: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n46: | `startRunTracker` return | `RunTracker` | Engine | Handle with `runId`, `runDir`, and the four tracker methods |\n47: \n48: ## Side Effects\n49: \n50: - Creates `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/` directory and `iterations/`\n51:   subdirectory on construction.\n52: - Writes `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/session.json` (full JSON state) after\n53:   every `recordEvent` call and after `finalize`.\n54: - Writes `.super-ralph/session.json` (global latest-run pointer) after\n55:   every `recordEvent` call and after `finalize`.\n56: - Appends one JSON line to `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/events.jsonl` for\n57:   each `recordEvent` call.\n58: - Writes `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/iterations/<NNN>-<label>.log` for each\n59:   `writeIterationTranscript` call.\n60: \n61: ## Failure Modes\n62: \n63: | Condition | Behavior | Recovery |\n64: | --- | --- | --- |\n65: | File system write fails | Exception propagates from the synchronous `fs.writeFileSync` call | Engine's `finally` block may not complete cleanly; artifacts are partially written |\n66: | `startRunTracker` called when `.super-ralph/` does not exist | `fs.mkdirSync` creates the full path (recursive) | No error; directories are created on demand |\n67: \n68: ## Dependencies\n69: \n70: | Dependency | Type | Purpose |\n71: | --- | --- | --- |\n72: | `src/events.ts` | internal | `EngineEvent` type used in `recordEvent` parameter |\n73: | `fs` | node | All file creation, writing, and directory operations |\n74: | `path` | node | Constructs paths within the run directory |\n75: \n76: ## Open Questions\n77: \n78: - The run ID format (`\"<timestamp>-<random6chars>\"`) uses a timestamp and\n79:   random suffix. The clock source and entropy source for the random component\n80:   are not documented in source.\n81: - Whether `writeIterationTranscript` writes `rawOutput`, `displayOutput`,\n82:   or both to the same file or separate files is not explicitly stated in\n83:   observable source comments.\n\n(End of file - total 83 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/modules/infrastructure/run-state.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Run State\n\n> Persists per-run artifacts: timestamped run directory, live `session.json`,\n> JSONL event log, and per-iteration transcripts.\n\n**Source:** `src/run-state.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe run-state module creates and maintains the file-based record of a single\nengine run. It is the write side of the run artifact system; `src/run-status.ts`\nis the corresponding read side. A `RunTracker` instance is created at the\nstart of each engine run and holds the run directory open for the duration,\nflushing state after every event and appending event records to an append-only\nJSONL log.\n\n## Triggers\n\n- `startRunTracker(projectDir, description, maxIterations)` â€” called by the\n  Engine at the beginning of every run. (`src/engine.ts`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180950891,"end":1772180950895}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180951266,"sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","part":{"id":"prt_c9e374f8a001kOTatI5fLkYf6X","sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","messageID":"msg_c9e374479001J2uXjvyO7QyS10","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_015z9s5xmdTKzMKDj7QTB1h5","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/config.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/config.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # config\n2: \n3: > Loads and merges `.super-ralph/config.toml` with hard-coded defaults, and\n4: > resolves the AI model to use for a given bead.\n5: \n6: **Source:** `src/config.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: The config module provides the single entry point for reading project-level\n11: configuration. It performs a deep merge of user-supplied TOML values over\n12: built-in defaults, so callers always receive a fully populated `LoopConfig`\n13: regardless of what the user has specified. It also centralises model\n14: selection logic, applying a three-tier priority: CLI override, bead area\n15: label, default model.\n16: \n17: ## Triggers\n18: \n19: - `loadConfig(projectDir)` â€” called during `setup` by every phase module\n20:   (via the Engine). (`src/engine.ts`)\n21: - `resolveModel(beadLabels, beadTitle, config, cliOverride?)` â€” called each\n22:   iteration by phase modules to pick the AI model for the current bead.\n23:   (`src/forward.ts`, `src/reverse.ts`, `src/decompose.ts`)\n24: \n25: ## Inputs\n26: \n27: | Name | Type | Source | Description |\n28: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n29: | `projectDir` | `string` | Engine / phase caller | Absolute path to the project root; config file is at `<projectDir>/.super-ralph/config.toml` |\n30: | `beadLabels` | `string[]` | `src/beads.ts` | Labels on the current bead, searched for `area:*` prefixes |\n31: | `beadTitle` | `string` | `src/beads.ts` | Title of the bead (used as a fallback label source) |\n32: | `config` | `LoopConfig` | `loadConfig` return value | Full merged config, used for `modelsAreas` and `models.default` |\n33: | `cliOverride` | `string \\| undefined` | CLI `--model` flag | Optional `\"provider/model\"` string that takes precedence over all other sources |\n34: \n35: ## Outputs\n36: \n37: | Name | Type | Destination | Description |\n38: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n39: | `loadConfig` return | `LoopConfig` | Engine / phase callers | Fully merged configuration object |\n40: | `resolveModel` return | `{ providerID: string; modelID: string }` | phase callers | Resolved AI model for the current bead |\n41: \n42: ## Side Effects\n43: \n44: - Reads `.super-ralph/config.toml` from disk synchronously.\n45: - If the file is missing, returns the hard-coded defaults silently (no error).\n46: - Throws if a model string (CLI override or config value) is not in\n47:   `\"provider/model\"` format.\n48: \n49: ## Failure Modes\n50: \n51: | Condition | Behavior | Recovery |\n52: | --- | --- | --- |\n53: | config file missing | Returns defaults; no error thrown | Caller proceeds with defaults |\n54: | TOML parse error | `@iarna/toml` throws a parse error; propagates to caller | Phase setup fails; run never starts |\n55: | Model string not in `\"provider/model\"` format | Throws `Error` with descriptive message | Phase setup fails |\n56: | No `area:*` label found on bead | Falls back to `config.models.default` | Model resolution always succeeds if default is set |\n57: \n58: ## Dependencies\n59: \n60: | Dependency | Type | Purpose |\n61: | --- | --- | --- |\n62: | `@iarna/toml` | npm | Parses `.super-ralph/config.toml` |\n63: | `src/types.ts` | internal | `LoopConfig` type definition |\n64: | `fs` | node | Reads the TOML file synchronously |\n65: | `path` | node | Resolves the config file path from `projectDir` |\n66: \n67: ## Open Questions\n68: \n69: - The deep merge strategy (user values over defaults) is applied recursively.\n70:   The exact merge semantics for array-valued config keys are not documented\n71:   in source.\n72: - `beadTitle` is accepted as a label source in `resolveModel` but the exact\n73:   mechanism by which it maps to an area is not confirmed from source\n74:   comments.\n\n(End of file - total 74 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/modules/infrastructure/config.md","metadata":{"preview":"# config\n\n> Loads and merges `.super-ralph/config.toml` with hard-coded defaults, and\n> resolves the AI model to use for a given bead.\n\n**Source:** `src/config.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe config module provides the single entry point for reading project-level\nconfiguration. It performs a deep merge of user-supplied TOML values over\nbuilt-in defaults, so callers always receive a fully populated `LoopConfig`\nregardless of what the user has specified. It also centralises model\nselection logic, applying a three-tier priority: CLI override, bead area\nlabel, default model.\n\n## Triggers\n\n- `loadConfig(projectDir)` â€” called during `setup` by every phase module\n  (via the Engine). (`src/engine.ts`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180951256,"end":1772180951264}}}}
