{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180953620,"sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","part":{"id":"prt_c9e37565d001hk4F1h576tofDT","sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","messageID":"msg_c9e37519b001OyZuB2RggtLKx1","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_013wZN69ujJLXW7EMNBxyxhj","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/engine/engine.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/engine/engine.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Engine\n2: \n3: > Implements the generic iteration loop shared by all three phases: server\n4: > startup, prompt dispatch, result classification, retry/skip/abort strategy,\n5: > event emission, progress logging, and run artifact tracking.\n6: \n7: **Source:** `src/engine.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The Engine is the single orchestration core of the framework. All three\n12: phases (Forward, Decompose, Reverse-autonomous) delegate their looping\n13: behavior here via `runPhaseLoop`. The Engine enforces iteration limits,\n14: applies error strategy, manages the opencode server lifecycle, and writes\n15: structured run artifacts. Phase-specific logic is injected through the\n16: `PhaseCallbacks` interface.\n17: \n18: ## Triggers\n19: \n20: - Called by `src/forward.ts`, `src/decompose.ts`, and `src/reverse.ts` via\n21:   `runPhaseLoop(projectDir, callbacks, flags, onEvent?)`.\n22:   (`src/engine.ts:runPhaseLoop`)\n23: \n24: ## Inputs\n25: \n26: | Name | Type | Source | Description |\n27: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n28: | `projectDir` | `string` | phase caller | Absolute path to the project root |\n29: | `callbacks` | `PhaseCallbacks` | phase caller | `setup`, `nextIteration`, `handleResult` implementations |\n30: | `flags` | `PhaseFlags` | CLI parser | `dryRun`, `maxIterations?`, `modelOverride?`, `attach?` |\n31: | `onEvent` | `EngineEventListener \\| undefined` | phase caller | Optional additional event subscriber |\n32: | `config` | `LoopConfig` | `src/config.ts` | Engine-level settings: `timeout_minutes`, `inactivity_timeout_seconds`, `iteration_delay_ms`, `strategy`, `max_retries` |\n33: | `PhaseIteration` | object | `callbacks.nextIteration` | Per-iteration data: `prompt`, `model`, `sessionTitle`, `iterationLabel`, `beadId?`, `systemPrompt?` |\n34: \n35: ## Outputs\n36: \n37: | Name | Type | Destination | Description |\n38: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n39: | Return value | `LoopResult` | phase caller | `{ completed, failed, skipped, totalTime, maxIterations, iterations[] }` |\n40: | Run artifacts | side effect | `.super-ralph/runs/` | Per-run directory with `session.json`, `events.jsonl`, iteration transcripts |\n41: | Progress log | side effect | `.super-ralph/progress.md` | One Markdown block appended per completed iteration |\n42: | Engine events | side effect | `EngineEventEmitter` | Typed events emitted at each lifecycle milestone |\n43: \n44: ## Side Effects\n45: \n46: - Creates and manages a `RunTracker` (via `src/run-state.ts`) for the\n47:   entire run: creates the run directory, writes `session.json` and\n48:   `events.jsonl` on each event, writes per-iteration transcript files.\n49: - Appends one progress block to `.super-ralph/progress.md` per iteration\n50:   via `src/progress.ts`.\n51: - Spawns an opencode server (via `src/opencode.ts`) unless `flags.attach`\n52:   is set, in which case it connects to an existing server.\n53: - Emits typed `EngineEvent` values to all registered listeners at each\n54:   lifecycle milestone.\n55: - Sleeps for `iteration_delay_ms` milliseconds between iterations.\n56: - In dry-run mode: iterates `nextIteration()` without running AI, emits\n57:   `loop.dry_run_iteration` events, and returns immediately.\n58: \n59: ## Failure Modes\n60: \n61: | Condition | Behavior | Recovery |\n62: | --- | --- | --- |\n63: | `setup()` throws | Error propagates to caller; no run directory created | Phase caller handles exception |\n64: | `nextIteration()` returns `null` | Loop exits cleanly; `finalize` is called | Normal termination |\n65: | Iteration completes with `failed`/`error`/`timeout` + `retry` strategy | Iteration counter is decremented; same bead is retried up to `max_retries` times | Automatic retry without user intervention |\n66: | Iteration completes with failure + `abort` strategy | Loop breaks immediately after calling `finalize` | Caller receives partial `LoopResult` |\n67: | Iteration completes with failure + `skip` strategy (default) | `failed` counter incremented; loop continues to next iteration | Next bead is attempted |\n68: | Wall-clock timeout (`timeout_minutes`) elapsed | `withTimeout` rejects with a descriptive error message | Counted as a failed iteration; error strategy applied |\n69: | opencode server fails to start | Exception propagates from `startServer`; `finalize` is called in `finally` block | Run is marked failed |\n70: \n71: ## Dependencies\n72: \n73: | Dependency | Type | Purpose |\n74: | --- | --- | --- |\n75: | `src/config.ts` | internal | Loads `LoopConfig`; provides engine-level knobs |\n76: | `src/opencode.ts` | internal | Starts or connects to the opencode server; runs prompts |\n77: | `src/progress.ts` | internal | Appends iteration results to `progress.md` |\n78: | `src/events.ts` | internal | `EngineEventEmitter` and `attachDefaultConsoleRenderer` |\n79: | `src/run-state.ts` | internal | `startRunTracker`; manages run artifact directory |\n80: | `src/timeout.ts` | internal | `withTimeout`; enforces per-iteration wall-clock deadline |\n81: | `src/types.ts` | internal | `LoopResult`, `PhaseFlags`, `IterationResult`, `ErrorStrategy` |\n82: \n83: ## Open Questions\n84: \n85: - The retry counter's exact bookkeeping (whether it resets per bead or is\n86:   global across the run) is not explicitly documented in source.\n87: - The `iteration_delay_ms` sleep is applied unconditionally between\n88:   iterations, including after the last one. Whether this is intentional\n89:   is not determinable from source alone.\n\n(End of file - total 89 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/modules/engine/engine.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Engine\n\n> Implements the generic iteration loop shared by all three phases: server\n> startup, prompt dispatch, result classification, retry/skip/abort strategy,\n> event emission, progress logging, and run artifact tracking.\n\n**Source:** `src/engine.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Engine is the single orchestration core of the framework. All three\nphases (Forward, Decompose, Reverse-autonomous) delegate their looping\nbehavior here via `runPhaseLoop`. The Engine enforces iteration limits,\napplies error strategy, manages the opencode server lifecycle, and writes\nstructured run artifacts. Phase-specific logic is injected through the\n`PhaseCallbacks` interface.\n\n## Triggers\n\n- Called by `src/forward.ts`, `src/decompose.ts`, and `src/reverse.ts` via","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180953613,"end":1772180953619}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180954140,"sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","part":{"id":"prt_c9e375a0f001m605Hewnyd9C4m","sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","messageID":"msg_c9e37519b001OyZuB2RggtLKx1","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01MurX8Jd4aE4vVHGJup3RRf","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/run-status.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/run-status.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Run Status\n2: \n3: > Read-only companion to Run State: resolves a run reference and reads back\n4: > session state, event counts, and transcript paths.\n5: \n6: **Source:** `src/run-status.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: The run-status module provides the read side of the run artifact system.\n11: It is used by the `super-ralph status` command to surface a human-readable\n12: summary of a completed or in-progress run. It reads the files written by\n13: `src/run-state.ts` without modifying them, and supports resolving runs by\n14: explicit ID or by the special reference `\"latest\"`.\n15: \n16: ## Triggers\n17: \n18: - `getRunStatus(projectDir, runRef)` â€” called by `src/index.ts:cmdStatus`\n19:   when the `--run` flag is provided. (`src/index.ts`)\n20: \n21: ## Inputs\n22: \n23: | Name | Type | Source | Description |\n24: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n25: | `projectDir` | `string` | CLI caller | Absolute path to the project root |\n26: | `runRef` | `string` | CLI `--run` flag | Either an explicit run ID or the string `\"latest\"` |\n27: \n28: ## Outputs\n29: \n30: | Name | Type | Destination | Description |\n31: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n32: | Return value | `RunStatus` | `src/index.ts:cmdStatus` | `{ runId, runDir, session, eventCount, lastEventType?, lastEventTimestamp?, latestTranscript? }` |\n33: \n34: ## Side Effects\n35: \n36: - Reads `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/session.json` synchronously.\n37: - Reads `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/events.jsonl` to count lines.\n38: - Reads the `iterations/` subdirectory listing to find the most recent\n39:   transcript file.\n40: - All access is read-only; no files are created or modified.\n41: \n42: ## Failure Modes\n43: \n44: | Condition | Behavior | Recovery |\n45: | --- | --- | --- |\n46: | `.super-ralph/runs/` directory does not exist | Throws descriptive `Error` | Caller (`cmdStatus`) prints error and exits |\n47: | `runRef` does not match any run ID | Throws descriptive `Error` listing available IDs | Caller prints error and exits |\n48: | `session.json` is missing from the resolved run directory | Throws descriptive `Error` | Caller prints error and exits |\n49: | `events.jsonl` is missing | Event count is `0`; no error thrown [INFERRED] | Status returned with `eventCount: 0` |\n50: | `iterations/` directory is empty | `latestTranscript` is `undefined` | Status returned without transcript path |\n51: \n52: ## Dependencies\n53: \n54: | Dependency | Type | Purpose |\n55: | --- | --- | --- |\n56: | `src/types.ts` | internal | `RunSessionStatus` shape referenced in return type |\n57: | `fs` | node | Reads run directories and artifact files synchronously |\n58: | `path` | node | Resolves run directory paths from `projectDir` |\n59: \n60: ## Open Questions\n61: \n62: - The exact sort order used to determine \"latest\" when multiple runs share\n63:   the same timestamp prefix is not documented in source. `[UNKNOWN]`\n64: - Whether `events.jsonl` line counting reads the entire file into memory or\n65:   uses a streaming approach is not confirmed from source.\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/modules/infrastructure/run-status.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Run Status\n\n> Read-only companion to Run State: resolves a run reference and reads back\n> session state, event counts, and transcript paths.\n\n**Source:** `src/run-status.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe run-status module provides the read side of the run artifact system.\nIt is used by the `super-ralph status` command to surface a human-readable\nsummary of a completed or in-progress run. It reads the files written by\n`src/run-state.ts` without modifying them, and supports resolving runs by\nexplicit ID or by the special reference `\"latest\"`.\n\n## Triggers\n\n- `getRunStatus(projectDir, runRef)` â€” called by `src/index.ts:cmdStatus`\n  when the `--run` flag is provided. (`src/index.ts`)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180954133,"end":1772180954138}}}}
