{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180955874,"sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","part":{"id":"prt_c9e376153001EdJiURah3MNZx7","sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","messageID":"msg_c9e375c5a001Ppw6CxiQfQT00w","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01HzUweb9e1NxehyRYEdahsn","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/progress.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/progress.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Progress\n2: \n3: > Appends human-readable Markdown progress entries to `progress.md` after\n4: > each iteration; reads recent entries back for agent context.\n5: \n6: **Source:** `src/progress.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: The progress module maintains a running Markdown log of iteration outcomes\n11: at `.super-ralph/progress.md`. The Engine appends one entry per iteration\n12: so that the AI agent in subsequent iterations can see what was tried and\n13: what happened. The same file is read back by phase `nextIteration` callbacks\n14: and injected into prompts as recent history.\n15: \n16: ## Triggers\n17: \n18: - `appendProgress(projectDir, iteration, result)` â€” called by the Engine\n19:   after each iteration completes. (`src/engine.ts`)\n20: - `readRecentProgress(projectDir, count?)` â€” called by phase modules in\n21:   their `nextIteration` callbacks to build prompt context.\n22:   (`src/forward.ts`, `src/reverse.ts`)\n23: - `formatProgressEntry(iteration, result)` â€” utility called internally by\n24:   `appendProgress`; exposed for testing.\n25: \n26: ## Inputs\n27: \n28: | Name | Type | Source | Description |\n29: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n30: | `projectDir` | `string` | Engine / phase caller | Absolute path to the project root |\n31: | `iteration` | `number` | Engine | Current iteration index (1-based) |\n32: | `result` | `IterationResult` | Engine | Outcome of the completed iteration |\n33: | `count` | `number \\| undefined` | phase caller | Number of recent iteration blocks to return; defaults to a module constant |\n34: \n35: ## Outputs\n36: \n37: | Name | Type | Destination | Description |\n38: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n39: | `readRecentProgress` return | `string` | phase `nextIteration` | Concatenated Markdown text of the last N iteration blocks |\n40: | `formatProgressEntry` return | `string` | `appendProgress` / tests | Single Markdown block for one iteration |\n41: \n42: ## Side Effects\n43: \n44: - Reads `.super-ralph/progress.md` synchronously in `readRecentProgress`.\n45:   Creates the file with empty content if it does not exist. [INFERRED]\n46: - Appends one Markdown block to `.super-ralph/progress.md` synchronously\n47:   in `appendProgress`.\n48: \n49: ## Failure Modes\n50: \n51: | Condition | Behavior | Recovery |\n52: | --- | --- | --- |\n53: | `progress.md` does not exist on first read | File is created (or read returns empty string); no error thrown [INFERRED] | `readRecentProgress` returns an empty string |\n54: | File system write failure in `appendProgress` | Exception propagates to the Engine | Engine's error handling applies; run may continue or terminate depending on error strategy |\n55: \n56: ## Dependencies\n57: \n58: | Dependency | Type | Purpose |\n59: | --- | --- | --- |\n60: | `src/types.ts` | internal | `IterationResult` type definition |\n61: | `fs` | node | Reads and appends to `progress.md` |\n62: | `path` | node | Resolves `progress.md` path from `projectDir` |\n63: \n64: ## Open Questions\n65: \n66: - The default value of `count` in `readRecentProgress` (when `undefined`) is\n67:   a module-level constant whose value is not documented in source comments.\n68: - `formatProgressEntry` includes `cost`, `tokens`, and `filesChanged` fields\n69:   from `IterationResult`. The exact format and units of the cost field are\n70:   not confirmed.\n\n(End of file - total 70 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/modules/infrastructure/progress.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Progress\n\n> Appends human-readable Markdown progress entries to `progress.md` after\n> each iteration; reads recent entries back for agent context.\n\n**Source:** `src/progress.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe progress module maintains a running Markdown log of iteration outcomes\nat `.super-ralph/progress.md`. The Engine appends one entry per iteration\nso that the AI agent in subsequent iterations can see what was tried and\nwhat happened. The same file is read back by phase `nextIteration` callbacks\nand injected into prompts as recent history.\n\n## Triggers\n\n- `appendProgress(projectDir, iteration, result)` â€” called by the Engine\n  after each iteration completes. (`src/engine.ts`)\n- `readRecentProgress(projectDir, count?)` â€” called by phase modules in","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180955867,"end":1772180955873}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180956304,"sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","part":{"id":"prt_c9e3762de001EETvN08b9Rla0y","sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","messageID":"msg_c9e375c5a001Ppw6CxiQfQT00w","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01PuKZxivmsjwLM4ghT1XZ9k","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/types.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/modules/infrastructure/types.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Types\n2: \n3: > Central type definitions: all shared interfaces and type aliases used\n4: > across the codebase.\n5: \n6: **Source:** `src/types.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: The types module is a pure declaration file with no runtime logic. It\n11: establishes the shared data model that all other modules depend on, ensuring\n12: a single source of truth for the shapes of beads, configuration, iteration\n13: results, phase flags, and error strategies. No functions, classes, or\n14: constants are exported.\n15: \n16: ## Triggers\n17: \n18: _Not applicable for this module._ The module contains no executable code and\n19: is never \"invoked\". It is imported by other modules at compile time.\n20: \n21: ## Inputs\n22: \n23: _Not applicable for this module._ Type declarations have no runtime inputs.\n24: \n25: ## Outputs\n26: \n27: _Not applicable for this module._ Type declarations produce no runtime\n28: outputs.\n29: \n30: ## Side Effects\n31: \n32: None. The module contains only TypeScript type and interface declarations.\n33: \n34: ## Failure Modes\n35: \n36: _Not applicable for this module._ No runtime behavior exists to fail.\n37: \n38: ## Dependencies\n39: \n40: | Dependency | Type | Purpose |\n41: | --- | --- | --- |\n42: | _(none)_ | â€” | This module has no imports |\n43: \n44: ## Open Questions\n45: \n46: - The `CompletionResult.status` union (`\"complete\" | \"phase_done\" | \"blocked\"\n47:   | \"failed\" | \"stalled\" | \"timeout\" | \"error\"`) includes `\"stalled\"` and\n48:   `\"timeout\"` as distinct values. The behavioral difference between the two\n49:   is not documented within the types file itself.\n\n(End of file - total 49 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/modules/infrastructure/types.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Types\n\n> Central type definitions: all shared interfaces and type aliases used\n> across the codebase.\n\n**Source:** `src/types.ts` (examined at commit `ecc95c0` / 2026-02-27)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe types module is a pure declaration file with no runtime logic. It\nestablishes the shared data model that all other modules depend on, ensuring\na single source of truth for the shapes of beads, configuration, iteration\nresults, phase flags, and error strategies. No functions, classes, or\nconstants are exported.\n\n## Triggers\n\n_Not applicable for this module._ The module contains no executable code and\nis never \"invoked\". It is imported by other modules at compile time.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180956299,"end":1772180956303}}}}
