{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772180971377,"sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","part":{"id":"prt_c9e379d10001KQRHYEbBSpFKct","sessionID":"ses_361cb8d0cffebVDrnflLw7abix","messageID":"msg_c9e379481001Q70Vtyiam4VsK6","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_011w56NgjLzxdStr4oLdRv9Q","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/architecture/runtime-lifecycle.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/architecture/runtime-lifecycle.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Runtime Lifecycle\n2: \n3: > Description of how super-ralph initializes, executes the steady-state loop,\n4: > and shuts down for each phase invocation.\n5: \n6: **Source examined at commit:** `ecc95c0` (2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Overview\n9: \n10: Every phase invocation (`reverse`, `decompose`, `forward`) follows the same\n11: runtime lifecycle managed by `runPhaseLoop` in `src/engine.ts`. The lifecycle\n12: has three stages:\n13: \n14: 1. **Initialization** â€” load configuration, create run artifacts, start server.\n15: 2. **Steady-state loop** â€” iterate: select, prompt, execute, evaluate.\n16: 3. **Shutdown** â€” finalize artifacts, close server, detach listeners.\n17: \n18: The lifecycle is the same regardless of which phase runs. Phase-specific\n19: behavior is injected through the `PhaseCallbacks` interface\n20: (`src/engine.ts:18`).\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ## Stage 1: Initialization\n25: \n26: ### 1.1 CLI Dispatch\n27: \n28: The operator invokes `super-ralph <phase> [flags]`. The shell wrapper calls\n29: `bun run src/index.ts \"$@\"`. Argument parsing in `src/index.ts` produces a\n30: `ParsedArgs` object (`command`, `positionals`, `flags`). Control transfers\n31: to the phase command function (e.g., `cmdForward` in `src/forward.ts`).\n32: \n33: ### 1.2 Phase Setup\n34: \n35: The phase command function calls `runPhaseLoop(projectDir, callbacks, flags)`.\n36: \n37: Inside `runPhaseLoop` (`src/engine.ts:24`):\n38: \n39: 1. An `EngineEventEmitter` is created (`src/engine.ts:30`).\n40: 2. A console renderer is attached (`attachDefaultConsoleRenderer`,\n41:    `src/engine.ts:31`). This listener writes events to stdout.\n42: 3. An optional external listener is attached if `onEvent` is provided\n43:    (`src/engine.ts:32`). Used for testing and TUI integration.\n44: 4. Configuration is loaded: `loadConfig(projectDir)` (`src/engine.ts:44`).\n45:    This reads `.super-ralph/config.toml`, merges defaults, and returns a\n46:    `LoopConfig` object.\n47: 5. `callbacks.setup(config, dryRun)` is called (`src/engine.ts:46`). The\n48:    phase determines `maxIterations` and `description`.\n49: 6. A `RunTracker` is created: `startRunTracker(projectDir, description,\n50:    maxIterations)` (`src/engine.ts:48`). This creates the run directory at\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 287. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"spec/architecture/runtime-lifecycle.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Runtime Lifecycle\n\n> Description of how super-ralph initializes, executes the steady-state loop,\n> and shuts down for each phase invocation.\n\n**Source examined at commit:** `ecc95c0` (2026-02-27)\n\n## Overview\n\nEvery phase invocation (`reverse`, `decompose`, `forward`) follows the same\nruntime lifecycle managed by `runPhaseLoop` in `src/engine.ts`. The lifecycle\nhas three stages:\n\n1. **Initialization** â€” load configuration, create run artifacts, start server.\n2. **Steady-state loop** â€” iterate: select, prompt, execute, evaluate.\n3. **Shutdown** â€” finalize artifacts, close server, detach listeners.\n\nThe lifecycle is the same regardless of which phase runs. Phase-specific\nbehavior is injected through the `PhaseCallbacks` interface\n(`src/engine.ts:18`).","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772180971370,"end":1772180971376}}}}
