`src/output-parser.ts` | Accumulated SSE text up to 250K chars |\n| `server` (`ServerHandle`) | `src/engine.ts:34` | Reference to the active OpenCode server process |\n| `finalized` | `src/engine.ts:50`, `src/reverse.ts:84` | Guard flag preventing double-finalize |\n\n### On-Disk State (persisted to filesystem)\n\n| File | Written by | Read by | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `.super-ralph/session.json` | `run-state.ts:writeState()` (every event) | `run-status.ts`, operator via `cat` | Live mirror of current run state |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/session.json` | `run-state.ts:writeState()` (every event) | `run-status.ts` | Per-run state snapshot |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/events.jsonl` | `run-state.ts:recordEvent()` (append) | `run-status.ts`, operator | Structured event log, one JSON line per event |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/iterations/<N>-<label>.log` | `run-state.ts:writeIterationTranscript()` | Operator | Per-iteration display + raw SSE transcript |\n| `.super-ralph/progress.md` | `progress.ts:appendProgress()` (append after every iteration) | `forward.ts:readRecentProgress()`, agent | Human-readable iteration summaries |\n| `.super-ralph/config.toml` | `init.ts` (once), operator edits | `config.ts:loadConfig()` | All runtime configuration |\n| `.super-ralph/*.hbs` | `init.ts` (once), operator edits | `template.ts:loadTemplate()` | Phase prompt templates |\n| `docs/specs/<name>.md` | Agent during `reverse` phase | Agent during `decompose` phase | Spec output of reverse phase |\n| `.beads/` | `br` CLI (via `beads.ts`) | `br` CLI (via `beads.ts`) | Task/bead data â€” opaque to super-ralph |\n| `AGENTS.md` | `init.ts:appendFileSync()` | OpenCode agent at startup | Agent instructions reference |\n\n### External State (owned by OpenCode server)\n\n| Entity | Where | Mutated by |\n|---|---|---|\n| Sessions list | OpenCode server in-process | `createSession()`, `abortSession()` |\n| Session messages | OpenCode server in-process | `runPrompt()` â†’ `promptAsync()` |\n| `task_complete` tool calls | OpenCode session message history | Agent during session |\n\n### State Transitions\n\n**`SessionState.status`:**\n- `\"running\"` â†’ `\"completed\"` (via `finalize(\"completed\")` when `failed == 0`)\n- `\"running\"` â†’ `\"failed\"` (via `finalize(\"failed\")` when `failed > 0` or on exception)\n\n**`IterationResult.status`** (per iteration):\n- `\"complete\"` â†’ increments `completed`, loop continues\n- `\"phase_done\"` â†’ increments `completed`, loop exits\n- `\"blocked\"` â†’ increments `skipped`, loop continues\n- `\"failed\"` / `\"stalled\"` / `\"timeout\"` / `\"error\"` â†’ applies `engine.strategy` (retry/skip/abort)\n\n**`BeadInfo.status`** (managed by `br` CLI, not directly by super-ralph):\n- `\"open\"` â†’ `\"in_progress\"` â†’ `\"closed\"` (transitions happen inside agent sessions via `br close`)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Configuration Sources\n\n### Source Hierarchy\n\nThere is exactly **one configuration source file** per project: `.super-ralph/config.toml`. There are no environment variables used for configuration, and no multi-file config layering. There is one CLI override mechanism.\n\n### Loading Code (`src/config.ts`)\n\n```\nloadConfig(projectDir)\n  1. Looks for: <projectDir>/.super-ralph/config.toml\n  2. If missing: returns DEFAULT_CONFIG unchanged\n  3. If present: parseTOML â†’ deep-merge over DEFAULT_CONFIG\n```\n\n**Deep merge specifics:**\n- `[engine]`, `[opencode]`, `[cli]`, `[reverse]`, `[decompose]` sections: spread-merge (config values override defaults; missing keys keep defaults)\n- `[models]`: flat string keys merged; the nested `[models.areas]` sub-object is extracted separately into `modelsAreas`\n- `[models.areas]` â†’ stored as `LoopConfig.modelsAreas` (area name â†’ model string)\n\n### Default Values (hardcoded in `src/config.ts:6`)\n\n| Key | Default |\n|---|---|\n| `engine.timeout_minutes` | `30` |\n| `engine.inactivity_timeout_seconds` | `180` |\n| `engine.iteration_delay_ms` | `2000` |\n| `engine.strategy` | `\"retry\"` |\n| `engine.max_retries` | `3` |\n| `opencode.url` | `\"http://localhost:4096\"` (not used â€” actual port is random) |\n| `cli.path` | `\"\"` |\n| `models.default` | `\"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"` |\n| `modelsAreas` | `{}` |\n| `reverse.output_dir` | `\"docs/specs\"` |\n| `decompose.include_review` | `true` |\n| `decompose.include_bugscan` | `true` |\n| `decompose.include_audit` | `true` |\n\n### Model Resolution (`src/config.ts:resolveModel`)\n\nPriority order (highest to lowest):\n1. `--model <provider/model>` CLI flag (applies to all iterations in this run)\n2. Bead `area:<X>` label â†’ `models.areas.X` in config\n3. `models.default`\n\n### CLI Flags (parsed in `src/index.ts`)\n\nAll flags are `--key value` or `--key` for booleans. Boolean flags: `--dry-run`, `--interactive`, `--fix`. All others take a value argument.\n\n| Flag | Affects |\n|---|---|\n| `--model` | `flags.modelOverride` â†’ passed to `resolveModel()` |\n| `--max-iterations` | Overrides `defaultMax` from `callbacks.setup()` |\n| `--dry-run` | Skips server start, agent execution, and `br` calls |\n| `--attach <url>` | Uses existing OpenCode server instead of spawning |\n| `--json <path>` | Writes `LoopResult` as JSON to the given path |\n| `--epic` | Forward/status: epic bead ID |\n| `--spec` | Decompose: path to spec file |\n| `--skill` | Reverse: built-in skill name or file path |\n| `--interactive` | Reverse: force interactive mode |\n| `--output` | Reverse: output directory for spec files |\n| `--answers` | Reverse: JSON file with pre-recorded mock answers |\n\n### Environment Variables\n\nOne env var is consulted:\n- `SUPER_RALPH_DEBUG` â€” if set (any truthy value), enables verbose debug logging of SSE events to `stderr` in `src/opencode.ts:200`\n\nNo other environment variables are read. API keys for AI providers are consumed by the OpenCode server itself, not by super-ralph.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Persistence and I/O Behavior\n\n### File System Reads\n\n| File | Module | Trigger |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.super-ralph/config.toml` | `config.ts:readFileSync` | Once per `runPhaseLoop()` call |\n| `.super-ralph/<phase>.hbs` | `template.ts:readFileSync` | Once per phase `setup()` call |\n| `.super-ralph/progress.md` | `progress.ts:readFileSync` | `forward.ts:nextIteration()` â€” reads last 5 entries per iteration |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<id>/session.json` | `run-status.ts:readFileSync` | `status --run` command |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<id>/events.jsonl` | `run-status.ts:readFileSync` | `status --run` command |\n| `.super-ralph/session.json` | Operator reads (no module reads it) | N/A |\n| `<specPath>` (any .md) | `decompose.ts:readFileSync` | Every `nextIteration()` call in decompose |\n| `docs/specs/*.md` (latest by mtime) | `reverse.ts:readFileSync` | `reverse:nextIteration()` on iterations > 1 |\n| `skills/<name>.md` | `skills.ts:readFileSync` | Once per reverse `setup()` |\n| `<answersFile>` | `interactive.ts:readFileSync` | Once at start of interactive reverse |\n| Templates in `templates/` dir | `init.ts:readFileSync` | Once during `super-ralph init` |\n| `.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` (source) | `init.ts:readFileSync` | Once during `super-ralph init` |\n| `AGENTS.md` (project root) | `init.ts:readFileSync` | Once during `super-ralph init` |\n\n### File System Writes\n\n| File | Module | Trigger | Mode |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `.super-ralph/session.json` | `run-state.ts:writeFileSync` | Every recorded event | Overwrite |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<id>/session.json` | `run-state.ts:writeFileSync` | Every recorded event | Overwrite |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<id>/events.jsonl` | `run-state.ts:appendFileSync` | Every recorded event | Append |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<id>/iterations/<N>-<label>.log` | `run-state.ts:writeFileSync` | After each iteration (if output) | Create |\n| `.super-ralph/progress.md` | `progress.ts:appendFileSync` | After every iteration | Append (create on first) |\n| `.super-ralph/config.toml` | `init.ts:writeFileSync` | `super-ralph init` (once) | Create |\n| `.super-ralph/*.hbs`, `AGENTS.md`, `intake-checklist.md` | `init.ts:writeFileSync` | `super-ralph init` (once) | Create |\n| `.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` | `init.ts:writeFileSync` | `super-ralph init` (once) | Create |\n| `.opencode/package.json` | `init.ts:writeFileSync` | `super-ralph init` (once) | Create |\n| `AGENTS.md` (project root) | `init.ts:writeFileSync` or `appendFileSync` | `super-ralph init` (once) | Create or Append |\n| `docs/specs/<name>.md` (or `--output`) | Agent (via OpenCode session) | During `reverse` phase | Agent-managed |\n| `<flags.json>` | `index.ts:writeFileSync` | After loop if `--json` flag given | Create |\n\n### Directories Created\n\n| Directory | Created by | When |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.super-ralph/` | `init.ts:mkdirSync` | `super-ralph init` |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/` | `run-state.ts:mkdirSync` | First run |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/` | `run-state.ts:mkdirSync` | Start of each run |\n| `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/iterations/` | `run-state.ts:mkdirSync` | Start of each run |\n| `.opencode/plugins/` | `init.ts:mkdirSync` | `super-ralph init` |\n| `tasks/` | `init.ts:mkdirSync` | `super-ralph init` |\n| `<outputDir>` (for specs) | `reverse.ts:mkdirSync` | First autonomous/interactive reverse run |\n\n### Network (External API Calls)\n\nAll network traffic goes through the OpenCode SDK to the OpenCode server (HTTP/SSE). Super-ralph never makes raw HTTP requests â€” the SDK abstracts all of it.\n\n| Operation | SDK Call | Module |\n|---|---|---|\n| Start OpenCode server | `createOpencode({ port: 0 })` | `opencode.ts:startServer()` |\n| Verify server health | `client.session.list()` | `opencode.ts:startServer()` / `connectToServer()` |\n| Create session | `client.session.create({ body: { title } })` | `opencode.ts:createSession()` |\n| Subscribe to SSE events | `v2.event.subscribe()` | `opencode.ts:runPrompt()`, `interactive.ts:runInteractiveSession()` |\n| Send prompt (non-blocking) | `v2.session.promptAsync(...)` | `opencode.ts:runPrompt()`, `interactive.ts:runInteractiveSession()` |\n| Abort session | `v2.session.abort({ sessionID })` | `opencode.ts:runPrompt()` (on inactivity timeout) |\n| Fetch session messages | `client.session.messages({ path: { id } })` | `opencode.ts:runPrompt()` |\n| Fetch session diff | `client.session.diff({ path: { id } })` | `opencode.ts:runPrompt()` |\n| Reply to question | `client.question.reply({ requestID, answers })` | `interactive.ts` |\n| Reject question | `client.question.reject({ requestID })` | `interactive.ts` |\n| Show toast | `client.tui.showToast(...)` | `opencode.ts:showToast()` (utility, not called from main loop) |\n| List sessions (v2) | `client.session.messages({ sessionID })` | `interactive.ts:gatherResults()` |\n| Session diff (v2) | `client.session.diff({ sessionID })` | `interactive.ts:gatherResults()` |\n\n### Subprocess Calls (Child Processes)\n\n| Command | Module | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `br ready --parent <epicId> --json --sort hybrid` | `beads.ts:getAllReady()` | Get unblocked ready beads |\n| `br show <beadId> --json` | `beads.ts:getBeadDetails()` | Get full bead metadata |\n| `br close <beadId> --suggest-next --json` | `beads.ts:closeBead()` | Close a bead |\n| `br show <epicId> --json` | `beads.ts:getAllBeads()` | Get epic's children |\n| `br list --all --json --id <id> ...` | `beads.ts:getAllBeads()` | Get full bead list |\n| `br create --type epic --title <t> --json` | `decompose.ts` | Create epic for decompose |\n| `br init` | `init.ts` | Initialize beads workspace |\n| `bun install --silent` | `init.ts` | Install OpenCode plugin deps |\n| `bun --version` | `index.ts:cmdDoctor()` | Health check |\n| `br --version` | `index.ts:cmdDoctor()` | Health check |\n\n### stdin/stdout/stderr\n\n- **stdout**: All engine events written via `console.log()`. SSE text deltas streamed character-by-character via `process.stdout.write()`. Heartbeat messages via `process.stdout.write()`.\n- **stderr**: Debug output when `SUPER_RALPH_DEBUG` set, error messages from `console.error()`.\n- **stdin**: Not read directly. In interactive mode, `@clack/prompts` reads stdin via its own TTY interface.\n- **Process exit codes**: `0` on success, `1` if `result.failed > 0` or any command-level error.\n\n---\n\n## 5. spec/ Directory Structure\n\nThe `spec/` directory contains reverse-engineered specifications written from source code observation, following strict clean-room conventions defined in `spec/CONVENTIONS.md`.\n\n### What Exists\n\n```\nspec/\nâ”śâ”€â”€ README.md              # Navigation guide, scope, artifact table\nâ”śâ”€â”€ CONVENTIONS.md         # Writing rules, confidence labels (CONFIRMED/INFERRED/\nâ”‚                          # ASSUMED/UNKNOWN), terminology table, required section\nâ”‚                          # template, markdown style rules\nâ”śâ”€â”€ module-catalog.md      # Inventory of all 19 modules, grouped into 5 domains\nâ”‚                          # (CLI, Phases, Engine, Integrations, Infrastructure)\nâ”‚                          # All modules currently have status `todo`\nâ”śâ”€â”€ architecture/\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ overview.md        # Five-domain architecture, module responsibilities,\nâ”‚   â”‚                      # all cross-domain interaction patterns, filesystem layout\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ runtime-lifecycle.md  # Stage-by-stage lifecycle (init/loop/shutdown),\nâ”‚                          # sequence diagram, config keys that govern lifecycle\nâ”śâ”€â”€ workflows/\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ core-workflows.md  # 7 named workflows (WF-01 through WF-07):\nâ”‚                          # init, reverse, decompose, forward, status, doctor,\nâ”‚                          # task_complete â€” each with trigger, preconditions,\nâ”‚                          # normal/alternate flows, failure outcomes, state changes\nâ””â”€â”€ modules/               # Per-module spec files (all 19 modules have a file)\n    â”śâ”€â”€ cli/index.md\n    â”śâ”€â”€ engine/engine.md\n    â”śâ”€â”€ phases/{forward,decompose,reverse}.md\n    â”śâ”€â”€ integrations/{beads,interactive,opencode}.md\n    â””â”€â”€ infrastructure/{config,events,init,output-parser,progress,run-state,\n                        run-status,skills,template,timeout,types}.md\n```\n\n### What the Module Catalog Says\n\nAll 19 module spec files in `spec/modules/` exist on disk, but `module-catalog.md` (written at commit `ecc95c0`, 2026-02-27) lists all of them as status `todo` â€” meaning the catalog predates the individual file creation. The architecture overview and workflows are fully written; the module-level specs may be partial or populated since the catalog was written.\n\n### Conventions Enforced by spec/CONVENTIONS.md\n\n- All claims must cite source file + line range or be labeled `[CONFIRMED]`, `[INFERRED]`, `[ASSUMED]`, or `[UNKNOWN]`\n- No verbatim code copying beyond 5 lines\n- Required sections: Purpose, Triggers, Inputs, Outputs, Side Effects, Failure Modes, Dependencies, Open Questions\n- File naming: lowercase kebab-case matching source filename (e.g., `run-state.md`)\n- Only `README.md` and `CONVENTIONS.md` may use uppercase filenames\n</task_result>"
